81
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:32,720
Early Arabic guzzle revolved around two broad themes.

82
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:39,320
The rakish celebration of wine, women and song and the elegiac lament over lost love.

83
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:45,280
By the time the guzzle passed into Persian from the early 11th century onward the second

84
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:49,200
theme had come to have mystical overtones.

85
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:53,440
Separation and suffering were at the heart of love and the faithful longing lover was

86
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,960
even a kind of martyr.

87
00:06:55,960 --> 00:07:02,040
Through Persian the medieval guzzle also came to develop major traditions in Turkish and

88
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,040
Urdu.

89
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:08,760
Nowadays among these languages the guzzle remains alive only in Urdu.

90
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:15,440
