00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:50,520
class backgrounds are amply documented.

150
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:55,840
All poetry is made out of other poetry but not all poetry is glad of it.

151
00:11:55,840 --> 00:12:00,880
The guzzle however delights in its huge treasury of earlier verses.

152
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:08,000
The very origins of Urdu poetry included macaroni or mixed Persian Urdu lines and verses.

153
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:12,560
The classical training for a poet included memorizing literally thousands of verses by

154
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:15,880
earlier Persian and Urdu-ostads.

155
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:20,360
There were various technical terms for the deliberate or inadvertent use of another poet's

156
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:22,800
line or idea or image.

157
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:26,960
If deliberate it was either a tribute or a challenge or usually both.

158
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:33,560
If inadvertent was it a creative coincidence, an innovative development or a vulgar imitation

159
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:40,120
