201
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:49,320
This is one of the enjoyable parts of the guzzle.

202
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:52,600
The lover is doomed, he dies, but it never stops him.

203
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:59,760
He doesn't shut up, he keeps right on composing poetry about what happens after his death.

204
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:06,160
The point is the transgressiveness, the liminality, the rush to break out of this flawed, doomed,

205
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:11,600
limited, worldly life into a larger, truer universe of passion.

206
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:17,640
The moth lying into the candle flame is thus one of the guzzles' emblematic images.

207
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:22,400
The burning, melting, self-consuming candle itself is another.

208
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:30,320
And the blossoming rose, whose smile is also her death warrant, as she blooms, is a third.

209
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:35,160
